# GH Actions parallel smoke matrix — design memo (CDX-S4, 2026-04-27T04:05:20Z)

## Trigger
- Add nightly cron `0 4 * * *` UTC; current `ci.yml` only has `push` and `pull_request` triggers, so this is additive. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:3-12`
- Add manual `workflow_dispatch`; existing live-smoke precedent is manual-only to avoid PR/push-triggered live mutation. `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:3-5`, `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:19-29`
- Gate the smoke job with `if: github.event_name == 'schedule' || github.event_name == 'workflow_dispatch'` so push/PR CI remains offline-only. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:65-69`

## Job structure
- Add one credential-bearing matrix job named `smoke-matrix` in `ci.yml`, with `needs: build`; the existing `build` job already depends on lint/typecheck/test/drift/examples/schema gates. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:164-167`
- Keep workflow permissions at `contents: read` for the first landing; both CI and current live-smoke use read-only contents permissions. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:14-16`, `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:31-32`
- Matrix axis `profile: [p1, p2, p3]`; CDX-1 defines profile IDs as the unit that owns test user, config path, sandbox folder, KSM app, marker channel, optional node, and title prefix. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:29-38`
- Matrix axis `scenario: [pamMachine, pamDatabase, pamDirectory, pamRemoteBrowser, pamUserNested]`; the registry contains six names, but `pamUserNestedRotation` remains preview/experimental. `scripts/smoke/README.md:51-58`, `scripts/smoke/scenarios.py:269-325`
- Exclude `pamUserNestedRotation` from nightly because it requires `DSK_PREVIEW` plus `DSK_EXPERIMENTAL_ROTATION_APPLY` and is not a live support claim. `scripts/smoke/README.md:38`, `scripts/smoke/scenarios.py:314-324`
- Use `fail-fast: false`, matching the existing Python test matrix behavior where one failure should not cancel sibling cells. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:45-51`
- Use `max-parallel: 3` for the first week, not 5, because CDX-2 recommends N=3 in CI and N>3 only with maintainer approval. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-2-concurrency.md:38-40`
- Add per-profile job concurrency, for example `smoke-profile-${{ matrix.profile }}`, with `cancel-in-progress: false`, so the five scenarios for one profile queue while p1/p2/p3 run in parallel. `docs/live-proof/README.md:31-33`
- Do not put a single `smoke-matrix-${{ github.workflow }}` concurrency group on every matrix child; same-group matrix children with cancellation would fight each other, while existing CI already has top-level cancel-in-progress behavior. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:17-19`

## Required L4 Preconditions
- Sprint 7h-38 must land `--profile <id>` before this workflow can run; CDX-1 proposes that CLI surface, while current `smoke.py` only parses `--scenario` and `--login-helper`. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:40-43`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:679-713`
- Sprint 7h-38 must either add `--parallel-profile` or drop it from the workflow command; it is not present in the current parser. `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:679-713`
- Per-profile state must cover at least test user email, Commander config path, sandbox shared folder, KSM app, marker channel, optional node, and title prefix. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:29-38`
- Current hardcoded single-profile state includes `testuser2`, `.commander-config-testuser2.json`, channel `sdk-declarative`, shared folder `SDK Test (ephemeral)`, KSM app `SDK Test KSM`, and project `sdk-smoke-testuser2`. `scripts/smoke/identity.py:27-39`, `scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:21-23`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:39-45`
- Current marker manager is a constant, so L4 should confirm whether per-profile marker isolation is implemented by manager name, manifest name, folder scope, or all three. `keeper_sdk/core/metadata.py:27-54`

## Per-job steps
1. Checkout with `actions/checkout@v4`; this matches existing CI/live-smoke checkout usage. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:26`, `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:43`
2. Set up Python 3.11; the package requires Python >=3.11, the CI matrix includes 3.11, and current live-smoke uses 3.11. `pyproject.toml:9`, `.github/workflows/ci.yml:50-57`, `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:44-46`
3. Install with `python -m pip install --upgrade pip` then `pip install -e ".[dev,ksm]" keepercommander pyotp keeper_secrets_manager_core`; smoke prerequisites list Commander, pyotp, KSM core, and PyYAML, while pyproject pins Commander/pyotp and has a KSM extra. `scripts/smoke/README.md:9-10`, `pyproject.toml:36-45`, `pyproject.toml:52-63`
4. Materialise `scripts/smoke/profiles/<profile>.json` from `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_<UPPER>_JSON`; CDX-1’s proposed loader reads `scripts/smoke/profiles/<id>.json` or env fallback. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:40-43`
5. Materialise the per-profile admin Commander config from `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_<UPPER>` to the path declared by that profile JSON; CDX-2 requires physically copied per-profile config because Commander rewrites config state in place. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-2-concurrency.md:38-40`, `scripts/smoke/identity.py:335-343`
6. Export `KEEPER_CONFIG` to the per-profile admin config path; EnvLoginHelper reads `KEEPER_CONFIG`, and CommanderCliProvider passes it to `keeper --config`. `keeper_sdk/auth/helper.py:224-229`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:176-180`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1657-1663`
7. Materialise admin KSM config from `SDK_SMOKE_KSM_CONFIG`; current smoke identity bootstrap is KSM-backed and the README requires an admin KSM config. `scripts/smoke/README.md:11-13`, `scripts/smoke/identity.py:367-391`
8. Provision identity with `python3 scripts/smoke/identity.py --profile <profile>` after L4 adds the flag; current identity CLI only supports `--force`. `scripts/smoke/identity.py:511-524`, `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:45-50`
9. Run smoke as `python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --profile <profile> --scenario <scenario> --login-helper env --parallel-profile` after L4 adds the new flags. `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:691-712`, `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:59-62`
10. Capture stdout/stderr to a per-cell log and always upload logs plus sanitized post-mortem JSON; current smoke prints a JSON post-mortem on failure and tails SDK stdout/stderr. `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:663-676`, `scripts/smoke/README.md:114`
11. Upload artifacts with 14-day retention; current live-smoke already uploads sanitized evidence with `actions/upload-artifact@v4` and retention control. `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:85-92`
12. On failure, emit a grouped section with the last 200 lines of the smoke log; current smoke already limits SDK command tails internally to avoid dumping full subprocess output. `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:459-487`

## Required secrets
- New: `SDK_SMOKE_KSM_CONFIG`, full `ksm-config.json` blob for the admin KSM path. `scripts/smoke/README.md:11-13`
- New: `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P1_JSON`, `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P2_JSON`, `SDK_SMOKE_PROFILE_P3_JSON`, one profile blob per lane. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:40-43`
- New: `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P1`, `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P2`, `SDK_SMOKE_COMMANDER_CONFIG_P3`, one isolated admin Commander config per lane. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-2-concurrency.md:31-40`
- Existing `ci.yml` has no credential-bearing env beyond offline `DSK_CI`; current live credential precedent is `live-smoke.yml` secrets `KEEPER_LIVE_KSM_RECORD_UID` and `KEEPER_CONFIG_B64`. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:65-69`, `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:10-13`, `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:39-55`
- Do not echo secret blobs; live-proof rules ban committed raw secrets and require secret-like captures to be sanitized before repo landing. `docs/live-proof/README.md:28-29`, `docs/live-proof/README.md:48-57`

## Concurrency Safety
- Current live-proof rule is still one live session/writer lane per tenant, with lock, queue, or different tenants required for parallel agents. `docs/live-proof/README.md:31-33`
- CDX-2 proposes relaxing that to one writer per profile per tenant only if profiles have disjoint `KEEPER_CONFIG` directories and marker channels. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-2-concurrency.md:46-49`
- S4 recommendation: implement GH job-level per-profile queueing plus in-harness profile locks, then update `docs/live-proof/README.md` in the L4 PR if the maintainer accepts per-profile writer lanes. `docs/live-proof/README.md:97-101`, `/tmp/dsk-cdx-2-concurrency.md:42-49`
- All 15 cells run on isolated GitHub runners, but tenant safety depends on profile isolation, not runner isolation. `docs/live-proof/README.md:31-33`
- The shared gateway is acceptable only as read-mostly shared state; CDX-1 says no per-profile gateway is needed for the smoke scope. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:64-69`
- Per-profile Commander config is mandatory because CDX-2 flags shared `~/.keeper/` as high risk, while the provider and helper both honor explicit config paths. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-2-concurrency.md:31-40`, `keeper_sdk/auth/helper.py:239-251`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1657-1663`

## Reporting
- Each matrix cell should write a small JSON result containing profile, scenario, exit code, smoke exit meaning, duration, and artifact name; smoke exit codes are 0/2/3/4. `scripts/smoke/README.md:70-78`
- Add a non-credential `smoke-summary` job with `needs: smoke-matrix` and `if: always()` to aggregate artifacts into `$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY`. `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:85-92`
- The summary table should group by profile and scenario because the scenario registry is explicitly resource-shape-parametrized. `scripts/smoke/scenarios.py:1-27`
- Optional follow-up: comment on a tracking issue only after deciding whether the workflow should get `issues: write`; first landing should stay `contents: read`. `.github/workflows/ci.yml:14-16`

## Cost Estimate
- Matrix size is 3 profiles × 5 supported/non-rotation scenarios = 15 cells/night. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-1-multiprofile.md:29-38`, `scripts/smoke/README.md:51-58`
- Conservative runner-minute ceiling is 15 × 20 minutes = 300 minutes/night, using current live-smoke’s timeout as the only in-repo timing bound. `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:35-38`
- Record actual p50/p95 duration in the first week’s summary before lowering timeout or increasing parallelism. `scripts/smoke/README.md:70-78`

## Risk + Rollback
- Risk 1: tenant concurrency policy mismatch; mitigation is either update live-proof rules for per-profile lanes or set `max-parallel: 1` until accepted. `docs/live-proof/README.md:31-33`, `/tmp/dsk-cdx-2-concurrency.md:46-49`
- Risk 2: same-profile scenario collision; mitigation is job-level per-profile queue plus in-harness lock. `docs/live-proof/README.md:31-33`
- Risk 3: Commander config collision; mitigation is per-profile physical config copies and explicit `KEEPER_CONFIG`. `/tmp/dsk-cdx-2-concurrency.md:38-40`, `keeper_sdk/auth/helper.py:224-229`
- Risk 4: secret leakage in uploaded logs; mitigation is sanitized post-mortem, live-proof redaction discipline, and a leak grep before upload. `docs/live-proof/README.md:48-57`, `.github/workflows/live-smoke.yml:75-92`
